    version: "v3.55.0",
    date: "2026-04-23",
    subtitle: "Downloader Slice 1: Seedable-Config, Setting-DB persistence, and the new `gitmap downloader-config` command (shorthand `dc`)",
    items: [
      "Added `gitmap downloader-config [path]` (alias `dc`) — the first slice of the planned aria2c-backed downloader. With a path it loads, validates, and persists a PascalCase JSON config; with no argument it walks an interactive prompt pre-populated from the current DB values (or `downloaderconfig.Defaults()` on a fresh install). Wired into `gitmap-v28/cmd/roottooling.go` via the existing dispatch table (no new branch in `dispatch()`).",
      "New `gitmap-v28/data/downloader-config.json` Seedable-Config carries the spec defaults: `PreferredDownloader=Aria2C`, `FallbackDownloader=GoDownloader`, `ParallelDownloads=15`, `SplitConnections=15`, `DefaultSplitSize=800K`, `LargeFileSplitSize=2M`, `LargeFileThreshold=100M`, plus the tiny-file profile (`TinyFileThreshold=2M`, `TinyFileSplitSize=100K`, `TinyFileSplits=8`) and the `AllowFallback` / `OverwriteUserConfig` switches.",
      "New `gitmap-v28/downloaderconfig/` package owns load / parse / validate / canonical-marshal / SeedHash. Validation enforces required PascalCase keys and clamps `ParallelDownloads` and `SplitConnections` to 1..64. The `\"auto\"` sentinel in `DatabaseVersion.LastKnownVersion` resolves to `constants.Version` at apply-time so the persisted blob always carries a real semver string.",
      "Storage reuses the existing `Setting(Key TEXT PK, Value TEXT)` table — no schema bump, no `SettingTypes` table. The full document is stored as a JSON blob under `Setting[DownloaderConfig]`, the seed file's hash under `Setting[DownloaderConfigSeedHash]`, and the gitmap version that last touched the DB under `Setting[DatabaseVersion]`. The `SettingType` enum (`DownloaderConfig` / `DatabaseVersion` / `SystemConfig`) lives in code in `gitmap-v28/constants/constants_downloader.go` so future tooling can route by category without parsing the JSON value.",
      "New `gitmap-v28/store/downloader_seed.go` runs the seeder both on full-pipeline migrations AND on the schema-version fast-path in `gitmap-v28/store/store.go:Migrate()`. The seeder hashes the canonical re-marshaled seed and skips when nothing has changed since the last apply, preserves user-customized configs unless `OverwriteUserConfig=true`, and falls back to `downloaderconfig.Defaults()` when the seed file is missing — so even a stripped-down deployment without `data/downloader-config.json` still gets a usable baseline persisted on first run.",
      "Reserved `CmdDownload` (`dl`) and `CmdDownloadUnzip` (`du`) constants alongside `CmdDownloaderConfig` (`dc`) so Slice 3 can wire the actual download commands without re-touching `constants_downloader.go`. Slice 2 (cross-OS `aria2c` installer + downloader engine with aria2c→Go fallback and size-based profile selection) and Slice 3 (the `download` / `download-unzip` commands themselves, with auto-install-on-first-use prompt and repo-URL→archive-zip resolution) follow when you say `next`.",
      "Bumped `constants.Version` to `3.55.0`. Schema version is unchanged at 20 — this slice adds only Setting rows, never new tables or columns, so existing installs upgrade transparently and the next subcommand is the one that triggers the seed.",
    ],
